[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_gqu0q")
reagent_id = "N2"
title = "Nitrogen"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]N₂[/cell]
[cell]Element:[/cell][cell]Nitrogen[/cell]
[cell]Atomic number:[/cell][cell]7[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]28 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Gas[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Odorless[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Makes up about 78% of Earth’s atmosphere.
• Very stable and relatively unreactive because of a strong triple bond between nitrogen atoms.
• Does not support combustion.
[b]Where nitrogen is found[/b]
• In the air.
• In proteins and DNA of living organisms.
• In many fertilizers.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of ammonia (NH₃) for fertilizers.
• Used as an inert gas to prevent unwanted reactions.
• Liquid nitrogen is used for cooling and freezing.
[b]Safety[/b]
Nitrogen is not toxic, but high amounts can replace oxygen in air and cause suffocation."
